cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper proposes an improved variant of RNN to capture and leverage local semantic structure information in natural language processing tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also introduces an attention mechanism and parameterizes structure information, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, respectively. Thus, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are also likely categories. Finally, the paper conducts experiments on language modeling, which involves text data and can be related to computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is also a possible category.
